    "description": "Access Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, provides IT solutions and products in Japan, America, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, Asia, Oceania, and internationally. It operates through three segments: IoT Business, Web Platform Business, and Network Business. The company offers browsers, including NetFront Browser BE, NetFront Browser NX DTV Profile, NetFront Browser HbbTV Solutions, NetFront HTML5 Platforms for Automotive, NetFront Browser BE for Automotive, and NetFront Console; and NetFront Agent, an IoT device used for date visualization, management, and control of IoT gateways. It also provides multiscreen products comprising ACCESS Twine, a 360-degree smart media platform; ACCESS Twine for Car, an automotive content and app service platform for connected car infotainment; NetFront Living Connect, a multiscreen media sharing for CE devices and home networks; and NetFront Living Connect for Connected Cars, a media sharing solution for automotive. In addition, the company offers PUBLUS, a digital publishing solution and PUBLUS Reader, an EPUB viewer; and network products, which include OcNOS, a network OS for white box systems; VirNOS, a virtual router network OS for NFV; and ZebOS, an embedded Network OS. It exports its products. The company serves telecommunications/broadcasting, TV operators, automotive, middleware, device manufacturer/OEM, OTT/internet service providers, publishers and education, and electric/gas/water industries. Access Co., Ltd. was founded in 1979 and is headquartered in Chiyoda, Japan."
